"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-01-Gymnast-Sunisa-Lee-on-her-aspirations-at-Paris-Olympics-2024-1vHyFYX0M7u-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Dan Williams  Copied  Gymnast Sunisa \\\"Suni\\\" Lee achieved a first three years ago in Tokyo, becoming the first Asian-American to win gold in the Olympics\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 All-Around competition.It came after teammate Simone Biles withdrew from the competition due to the \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099twisties,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 a mental block that causes gymnasts to lose their position while in midair.Lee told CGTN\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s Dan Williams that she is determined to defend her title and continue to inspire other Asian-Americans to follow their dreams.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"